section.section:
The application for the policy or notice of proposed insurance shall:
be signed by the debtor;
include:
the name and home office address of the insurer;
the name of the insured debtor;
the premium or amount of payment, if any, paid by the debtor shown separately for credit life insurance, credit health insurance, and credit involuntary unemployment benefit insurance;
a brief description of the coverage, including the amount and term of the coverage; and
a statement that the proposed insurance becomes effective under § 13-107 of this title on acceptance by the insurer;
refer exclusively to insurance coverage; and
be separate from the loan, sale, or other credit statement of account, instrument, or agreement, unless that document sets forth prominently the information required by this paragraph.
